  "A coffee shop sells lattes for $5 and cappuccinos for $4. On Monday they sold 50 drinks totaling $230. How many lattes were sold?": "",
  "20": "",
  "40": "",
  "25": "",
  "30": "",
  "Let L = lattes, C = cappuccinos. L + C = 50 and 5L + 4C = 230. Substituting C = 50 - L: 5L + 200 - 4L = 230, L = 30.": "",
  "A chemistry student mixes a 10% acid solution with a 30% acid solution to make 100 mL of a 22% solution. How many mL of the 30% solution are needed?": "",
  "40 mL": "",
  "50 mL": "",
  "60 mL": "",
  "70 mL": "",
  "x + y = 100 and 0.10x + 0.30y = 22. Substituting x = 100 - y: 10 - 0.10y + 0.30y = 22, 0.20y = 12, y = 60 mL.": "",
  "A farmer has chickens and cows. There are 20 heads and 56 legs total. How many cows are there?": "",
  "12": "",
  "14": "",
  "10": "",
  "8": "",
  "c + w = 20 and 2c + 4w = 56. Substitute c = 20 - w: 40 - 2w + 4w = 56, 2w = 16, w = 8 cows.": "",
